  "body": "### Note: \nThis is an issue created from the [Dark Labs AppCritique](https://appcritique.boozallen.com/) Static Analysis Report performed on Aug 14, 2018 on Status version 0.9.26 build 6382\n\nSome of these may be purposeful and taken care of.  If so, please provide reasoning here and it will be closed upon review.  This issue will then serve as a reference for future potential vulnerability disclosures. \n\n### Description\nThe app globally disables App Transport Security (ATS) for all\ndomains. ATS is a security feature which ensures the app\nestablishes secure network connections. The app can utilize\ninsecure HTTP connections when ATS is disabled, allowing\ninterception and modification of data by third parties. ATS is\nsupported in iOS 9.0 and later.\n\n[OWASP: 2016-M3-Insecure Communication](https://www.owasp.org/index.php/Mobile_Top_10_2016-M3-Insecure_Communication)\n\n### Platform\niOS nightly build: Status version 0.9.26 build 6382",
